Bhagwat Gita : Now some may argue that there many more text written in the same context. But the point here, the text is very much relevant today than any other time in the history and more practical when you want to apply it in your day today life.
Fascinating Stories : Now I am not saying other are boring, but nobody is more of real god than Krishna itself. The fact that Krishna birth was with full power and acknowledgment from part of Krishna make it more fascinating. The way he beats the best of bad mans, the way he beat even the gods ( remember indra ). The way he changes the rules of nature. ( Remember punardat life taken back from yama ).
Personal God : We are always looking to hear from real god, what were there view on this, what they would be doing in this situation. When the krishna being a personal god, acknowledging that he is only supreme god than all the talks suddenly start to make much more sense.
Love : He teaches you more love and bhakti than any other god in this world. At the end of gita, when he said come to me, I will take care of complete you, for a normal human being 18 chapters of Gita doesn't make that much sense than this one sentence. All the paths were cleared
